29/04/2011
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Nearly 4m euros in assets belonging to former Prime Minister Ivo Sanader have been frozen, the newspaper Jutarnji List reported on Thursday (April 28th). 
The anti-corruption office USKOK continues to investigate his wealth and bank accounts in Croatia and Austria. 
Sanader was arrested on December 10th in Austria based on an international warrant issued by Croatia where he is being investigated for possible criminal actions and abuse of power. 
(Jutarnji List, FoNet, Tanjug - 28/04/11)
